BOXING - HIDE REGAINS WBO CROWN BY BEATING TUCKER . Herbie Hide of Britain pounded American Tony Tucker to defeat in the second round to win the vacant World Boxing Association ( WBO ) title . The fight was stopped when Hide , the aggressor from the opening bell , knocked Tucker down for the third time in the round . The victory gave Hide , 25 , the title for the second time . He won it in March 1994 by knocking out compatriot Michael Bentt but lost it a year later to American Riddick Bowe , his only defeat in 30 fights . 
